On February 4, 2025, the Cabinet of Ministers adopted a decision on the allocation of  4.9 million euros to the Ministry of Finance – the Central Finance and Contracting Agency (CFLA), which acts as the Latvian Development Cooperation Agency:
(i) EUR 2.7 million: the restoration of Ukrainian social infrastructure facilities in the Chernihiv region in cooperation with the foundation "Entrepreneurs for Peace" and the association "Your friends"; 
(ii) EUR 1.5 million:  a grant tender for the renovation of infrastructure facilities in the Chernihiv region;
(iii) 100 thousand euros: the execution of construction work and their assessment at reconstruction objects; 
(iv) 400 thousand euros: the CFLA will also administer the "Center MARTA" project for the establishment and support of resilience centers in the Chernihiv region;
(v) 200 thousand euros: the integration of Ukraine into the European Union by providing SIA "Tilde" language technologie;
In this entry, we record the aid specifically directed to Chernihiv region, which is 4.6 million Euro in total.

On February 4, 2025, the Cabinet of Ministers adopted a decision on the allocation of  4.9 million euros to the Ministry of Finance – the Central Finance and Contracting Agency (CFLA), which acts as the Latvian Development Cooperation Agency:
(i) EUR 2.7 million: the restoration of Ukrainian social infrastructure facilities in the Chernihiv region in cooperation with the foundation "Entrepreneurs for Peace" and the association "Your friends"; 
(ii) EUR 1.5 million:  a grant tender for the renovation of infrastructure facilities in the Chernihiv region;
(iii) 100 thousand euros: the execution of construction work and their assessment at reconstruction objects; 
(iv) 400 thousand euros: the CFLA will also administer the "Center MARTA" project for the establishment and support of resilience centers in the Chernihiv region;
(v) 200 thousand euros: the integration of Ukraine into the European Union by providing SIA "Tilde" language technologie;
In this entry, we record the aid DOES NOT specifically directed to Chernihiv region, which is 0.3 million Euro in total.
